own 20 live "readme-techniques-count-drift — README techniques count matches actual"
  slug readme-techniques-count-drift
  decl README.md techniques/
  scope README.md 'NN Techniques' count must equal techniques/*.hexa actual file count.
  status live
  since 2026-04-21
  why Migrated from loop-rules.json#1 (2026-04-21). Prevents doc-vs-fact drift; keeps README number in sync with actual file count.
  drift_doc README.md
  drift_pattern (\d+) Techniques
  drift_actual find techniques -name '*.hexa' -type f ! -name 'test_techniques*' | wc -l
  cron daily
  on_fail warn
  label Techniques list count

own 21 live "readme-nexus6-tests-count-drift — README NEXUS-6 tests count matches actual"
  slug readme-nexus6-tests-count-drift
  decl README.md tool/own_nexus6_tests_drift.py reports/n6_selftest.json
  scope README.md 'tests: NNNN' count must equal actual test total (reports/n6_selftest.json#total).
  status live
  since 2026-04-21
  why Migrated from loop-rules.json#2 (2026-04-21). Original had echo 2078 stub and README never carried the 'tests: N' token — drift rule was orphaned from the start. Lifted to live 2026-04-24 with tool/own_nexus6_tests_drift.py (parity with own#20): authoritative source = reports/n6_selftest.json#total, README extraction = drift_pattern. WARN_NO_TOKEN when README has no token (SOFT, exit 0); DRIFT (exit 1) when a token mismatches.
  drift_doc README.md
  drift_pattern tests:\s+\d+
  drift_actual python3 tool/own_nexus6_tests_drift.py
  cron daily
  on_fail warn
  label NEXUS-6 test count
